ndiswrapper: ndiswrapper (Support for windows wireless drivers)
ndiswrapper: Many vendors do not release specifications of the hardware
ndiswrapper: or provide a Linux driver for their wireless network cards.
ndiswrapper: This project implements Windows kernel API and NDIS
ndiswrapper: (Network Driver Interface Specification) API within Linux
ndiswrapper: kernel. A Windows driver for wireless network card is then
ndiswrapper: linked to this implementation so that the driver runs
ndiswrapper: natively, as though it is in Windows, without binary emulation.
ndiswrapper: 
ndiswrapper: Note that if you are using a 64-bit kernel, you must use 64-bit
ndiswrapper: windows drivers with ndiswrapper.
